  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Virtual Reality Applications in Remote Handling Development for Tokamaks in India</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-13</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• The application of Virtual Reality (VR) in the design and operation phase of Remote Handling (RH) equipment for tokamak is evaluated and described. • A VR based centralized facility, to cater to RH development and operation, is setup at Institute for Plasma Research, India. • The VR facility system architecture and components are discussed. • Various VR applications, developed for design assessment, virtual walkthrough, compatibility assessment, RH equipment control, immersive viewing, haptic control and operation sequencing are presented.</subfield>
